From 2b0c041a0344c0bcad9cf7f7af272dc303ebb440 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:46:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.2b: Migrate 4 admin pages to useQuery
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Third slice of the T2.2 react-query fan-out. Migrates the four admin
CRUD pages (Members, Applications, Partners, admin SupportTickets)
from useState+useEffect+manual-fetch to useQuery + useQueryClient
invalidation.

Pattern applied:

  const { data = [], isLoading } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['<Entity>', 'list', { sort: '-created_date' }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.<Entity>.list('-created_date'),
  });

  // After any mutation:
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['<Entity>'] });

Page-specific highlights:

- Members.jsx: simplest case, single query
- Applications.jsx: two parallel queries (MemberApplication +
  scoped User pending). useMemo derives synthetic applications
  for pending users with no MemberApplication. Invalidation
  refreshes both queries.
- Partners.jsx: single query, two useMemo partitions (approved
  partners vs pending/rejected applications) replace two local
  state slices. Any mutation invalidates the single Partner key
  and both partitions refresh together.
- admin/SupportTickets.jsx: preserves useCurrentUser from T2.1,
  swaps useState+useCallback(load) for useQuery.

Mutations NOT converted to useMutation by design. Each handler has
meaningful per-handler logic (email side effects, partial-success
paths, confirm dialogs, bundled toast messaging) that stays clearer
as try/catch + await. A separate pass can consolidate to useMutation
once T2.2 fan-out is complete, if at all.

Design decisions in Applications.jsx:

- Synthetic app derivation moved into useMemo. Previously it ran
  inside loadApplications() every refetch; now it's a pure function
  of (apps, pendingUsersRaw) and only re-computes when either query
  updates.
- refreshAfterMutation() invalidates both MemberApplication AND User
  — approving changes a user's role, so the User cache must refresh
  to reflect the new state in other admin views.

Files (4):
- src/pages/admin/Members.jsx       (+15/-22)
- src/pages/admin/Applications.jsx  (+40/-42)
- src/pages/admin/Partners.jsx      (+19/-18)
- src/pages/admin/SupportTickets.jsx (+13/-16)

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 10 pre-existing warnings (unused catch 'e' vars)
- npm run build: succeeds
- All useEffect/useCallback removed from these files
- All load()/loadApplications() calls replaced with invalidations
